# Backend API base URL (no trailing slash). Leave unset in local dev to use Vite’s /api proxy
# (same origin → works with a single ngrok tunnel to port 5173).
# Set only if the API is on another host, e.g. a separate ngrok URL for the server.
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api-host.example.com
#
# --- ngrok (share dev app) ---
# 1) npm run server:dev  (API on 3001 — stays local; no second ngrok needed)
# 2) npm run dev
# 3) npm run tunnel  → open the printed https URL; /api is proxied to localhost:3001
# First-time ngrok: https://ngrok.com/download then  ngrok config add-authtoken <token>
#
# ERR_NGROK_334: your free-tier dev hostname is already bound (another terminal, agent, or
# dashboard session). Run  npm run tunnel:stop  and/or disconnect at https://dashboard.ngrok.com/
# Do not run  tunnel  and  tunnel:api  at once unless they use two different hostnames.
